  "text": "Problem model was introduced by Merkle and Middendorf in [CITATION_1] for a scheduling problem related to the JSS problem. In this model, we are given a decision variable for each position of a permutation of length . The domain of a decision variable is . Setting corresponds to placing operation on position of the permutation being built. The pheromone model is derived as follows from this problem model. For each combination of a decision variable and a domain value , we have a solution component , and for each solution component, we have a pheromone trail parameter . Using the mechanism of list scheduler algorithms, the solution construction process is as follows. Let denote the index of the decision variable that has to be assigned a value in the current construction step . The solution construction starts with an empty partial solution and with . [CITATION_2] This often corresponds to the problem model as it can be found in the literature.",
